Instructions
Start by cloning the starter code from the repo below into your development environment.

https://gitlab.com/cit_4640/wk5-packer-intro-lab-start

Complete the "web-front.pkr.hcl" Packer template in the repo to create an image the meets the following requirements.

Look for the "COMPLETE ME" comments.

Don't change any of the completed code, or scripts.

See the scripts and files for information on the location of files on your new image.

Make use of all of the scripts and files in the repo.

Your new image should: 
- Run Debian 13
- Have Nginx installed
- Serve the included HTML document using the included NGINX configuration file.
- When your image is completed you should be able to launch an instance and visit the included HTML document.

Deliverables:

Submit a link to a public Git repository that contains:
- your completed Packer template
  - and the included scripts and files directories, with the included scripts, html document and configuration files.
- an image(screenshot) in the README that demonstrates visiting the HTML document being served by a running instance of your image(AMI).
- demo your running instance in class.
